0 March|date=14 March 2020|work=The Hindu|access-date=15 March 2020|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n*'''On 15 March''', [[IIT, Bombay]] suspended all academic activities till 29 March.<ref>{{cite web |title=IIT Bombay suspends academic activities till March 29| url=https://wap.business-standard.com/article-amp/news-ani/iit-bombay-suspends-academic-activities-till-march-29-120031401159_1.html|website=Business standard|author=}}</ref> In [[Goa]] chief minister [[Pramod Sawant]] declared that all educational institutions would remain closed until 31 March. While the examinations of the 10th and 12th Goa Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary Education will be held as per schedule.<ref>{{cite web |title=Maharashtra Schools closed till March 31, all exams cancelled except for 10th, 12th Boards| url=https://www.timesnownews.com/education/article/school-holiday-updates-due-to-coronavirus-in-kerala-karnataka-jammu-kashmir-bangalore-delhi-mumbai-india/563653|website=timesnownews|author=}}</ref> [[Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation]] shut down [[Jijamata Udyaan]] till further orders.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/coronavirus-updates-live-total-number-of-coronavirus-cases-in-india-maharashtra-telangana-haryana/liveblog/74632927.cms|title=Coronavirus outbreak live updates: Mumbai cops invoke section 144 to ban group tours till March 31|date=15 March 2020|work=Times of India|access-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Gujarat]] government announced that all schools, colleges, cinema halls will be closed till 31 March, however the board examinations will be conducted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/breaking-coronavirus-gujarat-shuts-schools-colleges-covid19-598370|title=Coronavirus: Gujarat shuts all schools, colleges, cinema halls from tomorrow|last=Hardaha|first=Rashi|date=15 March 2020|website=www.indiatvnews.com|language=en|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref> [[Bihar Public Service Commission]] (BPSC) has postponed all the recruitment exams till 31 March.<ref>{{cite web |title=BPSC assistant engineer main exam 2019 postponed amid coronavirus outbreak| url=https://m.hindustantimes.com/education/bpsc-assistant-engineer-main-exam-2019-postponed-amid-coronavirus-outbreak/story-rQzUCoRWC4NHWa7Gq0SQTN.html|website=Hindustan times|author=| date=14 March 2020}}</ref> [[Vaishno Devi]] Shrine Board issued an advisory asking non-resident Indians and foreigners not to visit the temple for 28 days after landing in India.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-cases-in-india-live-news-latest-updates-march15/liveblog/74633220.cms|title=Coronavirus News Live Updates: Third case reported in Telangana|date=15 March 2020|work=Economic Times|access-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Tamil Nadu]] and [[Telangana]] governments declared closure of schools, malls and theatres till 31 March.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Narasimhan|first=T. E.|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/coronavirus-tamil-nadu-closes-schools-malls-and-theatres-till-march-31-120031500446_1.html|title=Coronavirus: Tamil Nadu closes schools, malls and theatres till March 31|date=15 March 2020|work=Business Standard India|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/coronavirus-schools-colleges-malls-movie-theatres-to-be-closed-in-telangana-until-31-march-11584186142495.html|title=Coronavirus: Schools, movie theatres to be closed in Telangana until 31 March|date=14 March 2020|website=Livemint|language=en|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> [[Ministry of Culture (India)|Ministry of Culture]] shut down all monuments and museums under [[Archaeological Survey of India]] till 31 March.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/all-asiprotected-monuments-central-museums-across-india-to-be-shut-till-march-31-govt/1763377|title=All ASI-protected monuments, central museums across India to be shut till March 31: Govt|date=|work=Outlook|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*'''On 17 March''', schools, colleges and multiplexes in [[Uttar Pradesh]] were shut down till 2 April and on-going examinations were postponed.<ref>{{cite web |title=All schools, colleges, cinema halls in UP closed till April 2 amid coronavirus pandemic| url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/schools-colleges-cinema-halls-in-uttar-pradesh-closed-till-april-2-amid-coronavirus-pandemic-598922|website=indianews|author=| date=17 March 2020}}</ref> [[Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation|BMC]] ordered private firms in [[Mumbai]] to function \"only at 50% of their staff capacity or face action under section 188 of the [[Indian Penal Code|IPC]]\".<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://m.economictimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/bmc-orders-private-firms-to-work-only-at-50-of-their-capacity/articleshow/74661516.cms|title=BMC orders private companies to work only at 50% of capacity as coronavirus count rises|date=|work=Economic Times|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Rajasthan]] government banned the gathering of more than 50 people in public places till 31 March.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus outbreak: Rajasthan bans all 50-plus gathering in public places till March 31, says official| url=https://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/coronavirus-outbreak-rajasthan-bans-all-50-plus-gathering-in-public-places-till-march-31-says-official/1900701/|website=financial express|author=| date=17 March 2020}}</ref> Important tourist destinations in [[Tamil Nadu]] were locked down. Authorities in [[Nilgiris]] district ordered the closure of tourist sites including [[Ooty]] and the tourists staying in hotels and resorts were given 24 hours to leave the city.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Tourist centres in TN under lockdown; Visitors in| url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/coronavirus-tourist-centres-in-tn-under-lockdown-visitors-i