of-coronavirus-cases-in-india-mumbai-hyderabad-kerala-pune-delhi/liveblog/74664459.cms|title=Coronavirus outbreak live updates: Railways cancels 76 trains as coronavirus precautionary measure, non-occupancy|date=|work=Times of India|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Mumbai Police]] ordered the closure of pubs, bars and discotheques till 31 March.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/mumbai/coronavirus-in-mumbai-eatery-industry-seeks-financial-relief-from-government/articleshow/74682915.cms |website=Times of India |accessdate=18 March 2020|date=18 March 2020|title=Coronavirus in Mumbai: Pubs, bars closed |first1=Reeba |last1=Zachariah |first2=S Ahmed |last2=Ali}}</ref>\n*'''On 18 March''', [[District magistrate|district magistrate and deputy commissioner]] of [[Srinagar district]] in [[Jammu and Kashmir (union territory)|Jammu and Kashmir]] said that the entry of all foreign tourists has been banned in the entire union territory.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Foreign tourists' entry banned in Kashmir| url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/coronavirus-foreign-tourists-entry-banned-in-kashmir20200318043955/|website=ANI|author=}}</ref> On the other hand, the Directorate of Floriculture, Parks and Horticulture of the state has also extended the [[Bahu Fort|Bagh-e-Bahu Garden]] to the general public from 18 to 31 March to keep the situation under control in the Union Territory.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Entry of foreign tourists banned in Kashmir| url=https://m.timesofindia.com/india/coronavirus-entry-of-foreign-tourists-banned-in-kashmir/amp_articleshow/74680062.cms|website=timesofindia|author=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Foreign tourists' entry banned in Kashmir| url=https://in.news.yahoo.com/coronavirus-foreign-tourists-entry-banned-kashmir-230952993.html?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAAsTPJ7Iu8cHV2-xuPg420W0USOlXiZxrTxRaDzUOSe5JdhiIz3IZSoNue88uI